01:05:42,949 --> 01:05:45,846
that your actions
have damaged the Monarchy.

964
01:05:47,594 --> 01:05:51,171
And that, one in four,
are now in favour...

965
01:05:51,172 --> 01:05:53,348
of abolishing the Monarchy
all together.

966
01:05:55,523 --> 01:05:57,159
As your Prime Minister...

967
01:05:58,166 --> 01:06:01,229
I believe it is my
constitutional responsibility...

968
01:06:02,262 --> 01:06:04,393
to advise the following...

969
01:06:17,382 --> 01:06:19,118
Is Queen Elizabeth up yet?

970
01:06:26,025 --> 01:06:27,142
Mummy?

971
01:06:29,074 --> 01:06:32,862
one.. fly the flag at half mast
above Buckingham Palace

972
01:06:32,863 --> 01:06:34,849
and all other
royal residences...

973
01:06:37,154 --> 01:06:41,585
two.. leave Balmoral and fly down
to London at the earliest opportunity...

974
01:06:42,330 --> 01:06:47,582
three.. pay respects,
in person, at Diana's coffin...

975
01:06:49,189 --> 01:06:52,898
and four.. make a statement
via live television...

976
01:06:52,899 --> 01:06:54,806
to my people
and the world.

977
01:06:56,723 --> 01:07:00,370
Swift prosecution of
these matters might, he felt...

978
01:07:00,371 --> 01:07:03,217
just might..
avert disaster.

979
01:07:04,469 --> 01:07:07,082
You will have to talk to the
Lord Chamberlain about all this.

980
01:07:07,083 --> 01:07:07,694
Well I have..

981
01:07:08,598 --> 01:07:11,483
and to Robert Fellows, and it
seems they both agree with Mr. Blair.

982
01:07:12,663 --> 01:07:13,632
Oh, I see...

983
01:07:13,633 --> 01:07:16,265
Something's happened..
there's been a change.. some...

984
01:07:17,086 --> 01:07:18,778
shift in values.

985
01:07:21,552 --> 01:07:22,993
When you no longer
understand your people, mummy...

986
01:07:22,994 --> 01:07:26,035
maybe it is time to
hand it over to the next generation?

987
01:07:26,036 --> 01:07:27,544
Oh, don't be ridiculous..

988
01:07:28,156 --> 01:07:30,543
remember the vow you took?

989
01:07:32,860 --> 01:07:36,391
I declare that my whole life,
whether it be long or short...

990
01:07:36,392 --> 01:07:38,498
shall be devoted to your service.

991
01:07:40,320 --> 01:07:41,308
Your whole life.

992
01:07:42,132 --> 01:07:44,015
That is a commitment to God...

993
01:07:44,016 --> 01:07:45,221
as well as your people.

994
01:07:45,222 --> 01:07:47,826
But what if my actions
are damaging the Crown?

995
01:07:47,827 --> 01:07:49,487
Damaging it!?

996
01:07:49,488 --> 01:07:52,948
You're the greatest asset
this institution has...

997
01:07:52,949 --> 01:07:55,582
one of the greatest
it has ever had.

998
01:07:57,347 --> 01:08:03,073
The problem will come when you leave..
but you mustn't think about that now...

999
01:08:03,170 --> 01:08:04,517
Certainly not today.

1000
01:08:04,518 --> 01:08:05,585
Oh, mummy..

1001
01:08:06,207 --> 01:08:08,209
You must show your strenght...

1002
01:08:08,949 --> 01:08:10,558
reasert your authority.

1003
01:08:12,869 --> 01:08:15,278
You sit on the most
powerful throne in Europe.

1004
01:08:15,279 --> 01:08:19,660
Head of an unbroken line that
goes back more than a thousand years.

1005
01:08:20,350 --> 01:08:23,931
Do you think any of your predecessors
would have dropped everything...

1006
01:08:23,932 --> 01:08:27,583
and gone up to London
because a bunch of hysterics..

1007
01:08:27,584 --> 01:08:30,834
carrying candles,
needed help with their grief?

1008
01:08:33,223 --> 01:08:34,718
As for that...

1009
01:08:35,328 --> 01:08:38,986
silly Mr. Blair..
with his Cheshire Cat grin...

1010
01:08:53,715 --> 01:08:55,529
Mr. Janvrin on the
phone for you, Sir..

1011
01:08:57,414 --> 01:08:58,825
Yes?

1012
01:08:59,246 --> 01:09:00,242
What?

1013
01:09:00,801 --> 01:09:02,265
I can't hear!

1014
01:09:04,121 --> 01:09:07,947
That's madness...
the whole thing!

1015
01:09:08,608 --> 01:09:10,083
Bloody madness!

1016
01:09:14,436 --> 01:09:15,696
I've just been told...

1017
01:09:16,962 --> 01:09:21,189
You've... decided to follow the
Prime Minister's advise...

1018
01:09:21,936 --> 01:09:23,626
I just want to say, I...

1019
01:09:25,367 --> 01:09:26,424
admire...

1020
01:09:29,563 --> 01:09:30,811
I think it's the right decision.

1021
01:09:32,581 --> 01:09:34,669
Let's hope we haven't
left it too late.

1022
01:10:20,223 --> 01:10:22,474
<i>Clearly The Queen
has had a change of heart...</i>

1023
01:10:22,818 --> 01:10:24,625
<i>she's clearly responding to
the need to feel...</i>

1024
01:10:24,626 --> 01:10:27,632
<i>that the royal family
is somehow engaged.</i>

1025
01:10:28,805 --> 01:10:31,878
<i>These are flowers that have been
brought to the gates of Balmoral...</i>

1026
01:10:31,879 --> 01:10:33,214
<i>so that she can actually see</i>

1027
01:10:33,215 --> 01:10:36,149
<i>some token, of what's been
expressed down here in London..</i>

1028
01:10:36,613 --> 01:10:38,667
- Fish Fingers.. do you want any?
- I'll be right there..

1029
01:10:44,323 --> 01:10:46,398
Thank God, for that!

1030
01:11:13,208 --> 01:11:16,989
<i>Britain's Queen Elisabeth will
deliver a televised address Friday...</i>

1031
01:11:16,990 --> 01:11:20,069
<i>the royal family has been accused
of not showing enough remorse...</i>

1032
01:11:20,070 --> 01:11:21,548
<i>over Princess Diana's death...</i>

1033
01:11:42,750 --> 01:11:44,476
Where are the boys?
Have they already left?

1034
01:11:44,477 --> 01:11:45,187
Yes...

1035
01:11:45,699 --> 01:11:48,096
they left for London,
after breakfast, with Charles.

1036
01:11:49,804 --> 01:11:51,413
It's not right, you know...

1037
01:11:51,414 --> 01:11:54,313
No, but further discussion
is no longer helpful, either.

1038
01:11:55,515 --> 01:11:57,007
Oh, well..

1039
01:11:57,961 --> 01:12:01,647
I suppose it does give the ghillies time
to find another stag for the boys.

1040
01:12:02,261 --> 01:12:03,893
- Now there's has been shot.
- What?

1041
01:12:04,534 --> 01:12:05,410
Haven't you heard?

1042
01:12:06,012 --> 01:12:08,083
He wandered over to one
of the neighbouring estates...

1043
01:12:08,084 --> 01:12:10,708
where one of the
commercial guests got him.

1044
01:12:14,846 --> 01:12:15,734
Oh.. really?

1045
01:12:18,024 --> 01:12:18,921
Which estate?

1046
01:12:36,688 --> 01:12:37,527
Here's your box.

1047
01:12:38,680 --> 01:12:40,980
There's some policy and
stuff in here that's important.

1048
01:12:40,981 --> 01:12:42,474
Have you seen the papers?

1049
01:12:42,475 --> 01:12:45,116
No, I thought I'd give them a miss today..
of course I've seen the papers!

1050
01:12:45,117 --> 01:12:49,531
Not bad, eh.. Your Majesty
have come down to London...

1051
01:12:49,532 --> 01:12:50,781
Who says that?
Tony Blair.

1052
01:12:52,969 --> 01:12:54,618
Mr. Father of the nation.

1053
01:13:10,959 --> 01:13:12,630
Ma'am...

1054
01:13:12,631 --> 01:13:13,781
- Good morning, Ma'am.
- Good morning.

1055
01:13:14,491 --> 01:13:16,822
Is it his Lordship,
you've come to see?

1056
01:13:16,823 --> 01:13:20,517
No, please don't disturb him..
I've come on another matter..

1057
01:13:20,518 --> 01:13:21,874
I hope you don't mind?

1058
01:13:43,126 --> 01:13:44,063
There he is..

1059
01:13:46,225 --> 01:13:48,617
a beauty, isn't he?

1060
01:13:49,302 --> 01:13:51,971
An imperial, Ma'am.

1061
01:13:52,563 --> 01:13:54,340
14 pointer.

1062
01:14:03,350 --> 01:14:05,311
- He was wounded?
- Yes...

1063
01:14:06,240 --> 01:14:09,992
We got our guest in very close..
had him lined up perfect.

1064
01:14:11,506 --> 01:14:12,664
And still...

1065
01:14:13,462 --> 01:14:16,195
an investment banker, Ma'am..
from London.

1066
01:14:16,806 --> 01:14:20,448
I'm afraid the stalkers had to
follow him for miles, to finish him off..

1067
01:14:23,705 --> 01:14:25,741
Let's hope he didn't suffer too much.

1068
01:14:36,044 --> 01:14:38,406
Please pass my congratulations,
to your guest.

1069
01:14:38,407 --> 01:14:39,292
I will, Ma'am...

1070
01:14:46,744 --> 01:14:48,233
God bless you, Ma'am.

1071
01:14:48,362 --> 01:14:49,473
Thank you.

1072
01:15:21,565 --> 01:15:24,017
- Ma'am?
- Yes, Robin...

1073
01:15:24,018 --> 01:15:26,939
I've done a draft,
of your television address.

1074
01:15:26,940 --> 01:15:27,988
Thank you.

1075
01:15:32,424 --> 01:15:34,038
Was there anything else?

1076
01:15:35,315 --> 01:15:36,512
No, Ma'am.

1077
01:15:37,121 --> 01:15:39,479
Landing in 15 minutes.

1078
01:15:50,690 --> 01:15:51,983
I've got The Queen's speech.

1079
01:15:53,985 --> 01:15:56,625
- Shall I give Tony a copy?
- No, let me have a look at it first...

1080
01:15:56,626 --> 01:15:57,626
- He's next door.

1081
01:16:46,744 --> 01:16:51,301
<i>The Queen is getting out of the car...
and is going to talk to people.</i>

1082
01:16:51,747 --> 01:16:55,151
<i>It's extremely unusual..
this is almost unprecedented..</i>

1083
01:16:55,152 --> 01:16:58,555
<i>I think perhaps the last time
The Queen was among her people...</i>

1084
01:16:58,556 --> 01:17:02,677
<i>outside the Palace..
was the day the war in Europe ended.</i>

1085
01:17:24,493 --> 01:17:26,586
They sent a copy
of The Queen's speech...

1086
01:17:28,557 --> 01:17:30,717
Well, let's get the frost off it first.

1087
01:17:38,757 --> 01:17:40,818
I've phoned them
with a couple of suggestions...

1088
01:17:41,575 --> 01:17:43,320
to make it sound like it
came from a human being.

1089
01:17:43,321 --> 01:17:44,233
Yeah, alright Alastair..

1090
01:17:46,767 --> 01:17:49,969
Well at least the old bat has
finally agreed to visit Diana's coffin.

1091
01:17:49,970 --> 01:17:52,475
When you get it wrong,
you really get it wrong...

1092
01:17:53,038 --> 01:17:57,038
that woman has given her
whole life in service to her people.

1093
01:17:57,039 --> 01:17:59,675
50 years doing the job,
she never wanted...

1094
01:17:59,676 --> 01:18:01,686
a job she watched kill her father...

1095
01:18:01,687 --> 01:18:06,112
she's executed it with honour, dignity,
and as far as I could tell...

1096
01:18:06,113 --> 01:18:08,923
without a single blemish,
and now we're all baying for her blood.

1097
01:18:08,924 --> 01:18:11,702
All because she's struggling
to lead the world in mourning

1098
01:18:11,703 --> 01:18:14,481
for someone who threw everything
she offered back in her face.

1099
01:18:14,482 --> 01:18:17,227
and who for the last few years
seemed commited 24/7

1100
01:18:17,228 --> 01:18:19,972
to destroying everything
she holds most dear.

1101
01:19:22,515 --> 01:19:25,642
Hello.. would you like
me to place those for you?

1102
01:19:25,643 --> 01:19:26,707
No...

1103
01:19:27,410 --> 01:19:28,636
Oh...

1104
01:19:29,147 --> 01:19:30,210
These are for you.

1105
01:19:33,029 --> 01:19:34,011
For me?

1106
01:19:37,972 --> 01:19:38,878
Thank you.

1107
01:19:40,487 --> 01:19:42,232
Thank you very much.

1108
01:20:12,013 --> 01:20:14,577
There's been a last minute
addition from Downing Street.

1109
01:20:14,578 --> 01:20:17,143
They're suggesting adding,
'and as a grandmother'...

1110
01:20:17,690 --> 01:20:18,867
here.
- Right.

1111
01:20:23,854 --> 01:20:27,965
So what I say to you now, as
your Queen, and as a grandmother...

1112
01:20:28,585 --> 01:20:30,577
I say from my heart.

1113
01:20:31,445 --> 01:20:32,466
You think you can say it?

1114
01:20:33,214 --> 01:20:36,541
- Do I have a choice?
- We're ready for you, Your Majesty.

1115
01:20:39,156 --> 01:20:42,051
Just to confirm,
this is going out live.

1116
01:20:42,052 --> 01:20:43,845
- Fine.
- And you'll be at the front of

1117
01:20:43,846 --> 01:20:45,638
the 6 o'clock news..
on all the channels.

1118
01:20:45,639 --> 01:20:47,048
Yes.

1119
01:21:28,848 --> 01:21:31,024
<i>- Okay, nice and quiet..
- Ten seconds, everyone!</i>

1120
01:21:34,556 --> 01:21:38,061
<i>We cross now, live,
to Buckingham Palace...</i>

1121
01:21:38,062 --> 01:21:40,587
<i>for the Queen's tribute
to Princess Diana.</i>

1122
01:21:46,413 --> 01:21:49,254
Since last Sundays'
dreadful news...

1123
01:21:49,255 --> 01:21:51,920
we have seen throughout Britain,
and around the world...

1124
01:21:51,920 --> 01:21:55,846
an overwhelming expression
of sadness at Diana's death.

1125
01:21:57,634 --> 01:22:00,929
We have all been trying,
in our different ways, to cope...

1126
01:22:01,796 --> 01:22:04,322
it is not easy
to express a sense of loss...

1127
01:22:04,323 --> 01:22:06,689
since the initial shock,
is often succeeded

1128
01:22:06,690 --> 01:22:08,655
by a mixture
of other feelings...

1129
01:22:08,656 --> 01:22:13,871
disbelief, incomprehension, anger..
and concern for those who remain.

1130
01:22:16,153 --> 01:22:20,168
We have all felt those
emotions in these last few days...

1131
01:22:20,169 --> 01:22:24,422
so what I say to you now,
as your Queen, and as a grandmother...

1132
01:22:25,116 --> 01:22:27,699
I say from my heart.

1133
01:22:27,700 --> 01:22:30,002
Heart..
What heart?

1134
01:22:30,383 --> 01:22:31,910
She doesn't mean a word of this.

1135
01:22:32,517 --> 01:22:35,215
That's not the point.
What she's doing is extraordinary.

1136
01:22:37,454 --> 01:22:39,175
That's how to survive.

1137
01:22:39,176 --> 01:22:40,450
Listen to you..

1138
01:22:40,451 --> 01:22:43,725
a week ago you were the
great moderniser...

1139
01:22:43,726 --> 01:22:46,233
making speeches
about the people's Princess.

1140
01:22:46,792 --> 01:22:48,706
Now you've gone weak at the knees.

1141
01:22:50,830 --> 01:22:54,663
You know.. I don't know
why I'm so surprised..

1142
01:22:55,362 --> 01:22:57,307
at the end of the day,
all Labour Prime Ministers...

1143
01:22:57,308 --> 01:23:00,452
go ga-ga for the Queen.

1144
01:23:00,453 --> 01:23:01,494
What?

1145
01:23:07,189 --> 01:23:12,264
I, for one, believe that there are
lessons to be drawn from her life...

1146
01:23:12,265 --> 01:23:15,834
and from the extraordinary,
and moving, reaction to her death.

1147
01:23:17,145 --> 01:23:20,777
I share in your determination,
to cherish her memory.

1148
01:23:21,436 --> 01:23:25,277
I hope that tomorrow we
can all, wherever we are...

1149
01:23:25,278 --> 01:23:28,876
join in expressing our grief,
at Diana's loss...

1150
01:23:28,877 --> 01:23:31,857
and gratitude for her
all too short life.

1151
01:23:32,733 --> 01:23:35,223
May those who died,
rest in peace...

1152
01:23:35,224 --> 01:23:38,210
and may we,
each and everyone of us...

1153
01:23:38,211 --> 01:23:43,678
thank God, for someone who
made many, many people, happy.

1154
01:23:50,529 --> 01:23:53,321
<i>Diana's coffin, now on the move...</i>

1155
01:23:53,322 --> 01:23:55,486
<i>the short distance
from St. James' Palace...</i>

1156
01:23:55,487 --> 01:23:58,850
<i>to her home at Kensington
Palace, for the final night...</i>

1157
01:23:58,859 --> 01:24:00,589
<i>before her burial tomorrow.</i>

1158
01:24:02,307 --> 01:24:03,305
<i>It's incredible...</i>

1159
01:24:03,306 --> 01:24:05,046
<i>less than a week.</i>

1160
01:24:05,539 --> 01:24:07,481
<i>Who could have imagined,
such scenes?</i>

1161
01:25:19,847 --> 01:25:23,485
Diana was the very essence
of compassion, of duty...

1162
01:25:23,486 --> 01:25:26,007
of style, of beauty.

1163
01:25:26,008 --> 01:25:28,192
A very British girl...

1164
01:25:28,193 --> 01:25:30,347
who transcended nationality.

1165
01:25:31,050 --> 01:25:33,156
Someone with
a natural nobility...

1166
01:25:33,157 --> 01:25:36,689
who was classless, and who
proved in the last year...

1167
01:25:36,690 --> 01:25:40,163
that she needed no royal title
to continue to generate...

1168
01:25:40,164 --> 01:25:42,032
a particular brand of magic.

1169
01:25:46,160 --> 01:25:48,275
I would like to end by,
thanking God...

1170
01:25:48,276 --> 01:25:50,990
for the small mercies he's
shown us at this dreadful time...

1171
01:25:52,103 --> 01:25:55,088
for taking Diana at
her most beautiful and radiant.

1172
01:25:55,089 --> 01:25:57,297
And when she had joy,
in her private life.

1173
01:25:58,299 --> 01:26:00,681
Above all, we give thanks
for the life of a woman...

1174
01:26:00,682 --> 01:26:03,363
I'm so proud
to be able to call my sister.

1175
01:26:03,364 --> 01:26:06,218
The uniqe, the complexed...

1176
01:26:06,219 --> 01:26:09,225
the extraordinary,
and irreplaceable, Diana.

1177
01:26:09,731 --> 01:26:12,637
Who's beauty, both internal
and external...

1178
01:26:12,638 --> 01:26:15,457
will never be extinguished
from our minds.

1179
01:27:08,449 --> 01:27:13,672
- So, off to see your girlfriend?
- Now, now.

1180
01:27:14,921 --> 01:27:17,023
You know, I hope she
shows you some respect this time.

1181
01:27:17,748 --> 01:27:19,863
It's quite a debt of gratitude,
she owes you.

1182
01:27:20,613 --> 01:27:22,982
Mr. Saviour of the Monarchy.

1183
01:27:23,701 --> 01:27:25,512
I doubt she'll see it that way..

1184
01:27:30,887 --> 01:27:32,784
- Robin.. good to see you.
- Prime Minister.

1185
01:27:32,784 --> 01:27:33,697
Tony, please.

1186
01:27:44,584 --> 01:27:45,805
The Prime Minister,
Your Majesty.

1187
01:27:54,654 --> 01:27:55,542
Do sit down.

1188
01:27:56,443 --> 01:27:57,643
Thank you.

1189
01:28:09,332 --> 01:28:10,529
It's good to see you again.

1190
01:28:11,917 --> 01:28:14,915
After what's been..
quite a summer.

1191
01:28:15,382 --> 01:28:17,817
I'm refering to your visit
to India.. and Pakistan.

1192
01:28:18,578 --> 01:28:21,181
Where your comments on
ending historic disagreements...

1193
01:28:21,182 --> 01:28:22,985
went down very well.

1194
01:28:24,739 --> 01:28:26,644
On the commonwealth heads
of government meeting...

1195
01:28:28,432 --> 01:28:29,836
I spoke to the Prime Minister of Malawi...

1196
01:28:29,837 --> 01:28:32,244
and he was saying
how much he appreciated your...

1197
01:28:32,245 --> 01:28:34,653
tough stands on Nigeria...

1198
01:28:34,654 --> 01:28:36,421
I meant to tell you at the time, but...

1199
01:28:38,069 --> 01:28:39,827
you were being monopolised, rather...

1200
01:28:43,066 --> 01:28:45,265
I imagine those occations
must be quite difficult.

1201
01:28:46,751 --> 01:28:50,457
24 heads of government, each
clamouring for a private audience.

1202
01:28:54,732 --> 01:28:59,201
Also we have another
chance to speak, since.. that week.

1203
01:29:02,247 --> 01:29:04,223
And I wanted to offer my apologies.

1204
01:29:04,223 --> 01:29:05,579
Whatever for?

1205
01:29:05,580 --> 01:29:10,018
In case you felt manhandled, or..
managed, in any way.

1206
01:29:10,184 --> 01:29:11,376
No, not at all.

1207
01:29:16,973 --> 01:29:20,497
I don't think I shall ever understand,
what happened this summer.

1208
01:29:20,497 --> 01:29:24,581
Well.. the circumstances
were exceptional, Ma'am..

1209
01:29:25,398 --> 01:29:28,546
and in the end you
showed great personal strenght...

1210
01:29:29,247 --> 01:29:31,045
courage and humility.

1211
01:29:31,439 --> 01:29:33,588
You're confusing humility,
with humiliation.

1212
01:29:33,589 --> 01:29:35,033
That's not true.

1213
01:29:35,034 --> 01:29:38,897
You didn't read the cards on the
flowers outside the Palace, that Friday.

1214
01:29:39,718 --> 01:29:42,813
I actually think history will show,
it was a good week for you.

1215
01:29:42,814 --> 01:29:44,764
And an even better one
for you, Mr. Blair.

1216
01:29:45,971 --> 01:29:48,023
But there are 52 weeks
in the year, Ma'am...

1217
01:29:48,024 --> 01:29:52,844
and 2500 in the time
since you've been Queen.

1218
01:29:55,787 --> 01:29:58,340
And when people come
to assess your legacy...

1219
01:29:58,341 --> 01:30:00,475
they won't remember those few days.
- Oh, really?

1220
01:30:02,301 --> 01:30:05,438
You don't think what affection
people once had for...

1221
01:30:06,957 --> 01:30:08,217
for this institution...

1222
01:30:09,294 --> 01:30:10,315
has been diminished?

1223
01:30:10,316 --> 01:30:11,323
No...

1224
01:30:11,324 --> 01:30:12,651
not at all.

1225
01:30:13,476 --> 01:30:15,695
You're more respected now,
than ever...

1226
01:30:15,696 --> 01:30:19,510
I gather some of your closest advisers
were less fulsome in their support.

1227
01:30:20,760 --> 01:30:22,252
One or two...

1228
01:30:22,967 --> 01:30:27,018
but as a leader, I could never
have added my voice to that chorus.

1229
01:30:27,019 --> 01:30:28,143
Because you saw those headlines,
and you thought...

1230
01:30:28,144 --> 01:30:30,268
one day that might happen to me.

1231
01:30:33,039 --> 01:30:34,421
And it will, Mr. Blair.

1232
01:30:35,015 --> 01:30:37,033
Quite suddenly, and without warning.

1233
01:30:39,868 --> 01:30:42,289
So.. shall we get on
with the business in hand?

1234
01:30:44,302 --> 01:30:45,438
Oh, look...

1235
01:30:47,202 --> 01:30:49,733
I do love this time of day.

1236
01:30:49,734 --> 01:30:51,638
Shall we walk, while there is still light?

1237
01:30:51,639 --> 01:30:54,526
You know the clocks go back
next week, it will be dark before five.

1238
01:30:55,011 --> 01:30:57,613
- I do hope you're a walker?
- I am...

1239
01:30:57,614 --> 01:31:00,624
Good.. I always think these meetings
have a far greater chance of success...

1240
01:31:00,625 --> 01:31:02,635
if the Prime Minister is a walker.

1241
01:31:03,683 --> 01:31:05,693
As a matter of fact,  that's
how I think best.. on my feet..

1242
01:31:05,694 --> 01:31:08,705
I've never been one
for sitting around endlessly...

1243
01:31:08,706 --> 01:31:11,283
a good walk and fresh air
sorts everything out.

1244
01:31:16,533 --> 01:31:19,810
One in four.. you said..
wanted to get rid of me.

1245
01:31:19,811 --> 01:31:21,512
For about half an hour.

1246
01:31:22,220 --> 01:31:23,320
But then...

1247
01:31:23,321 --> 01:31:26,470
you came down to London,
and all that went away.

1248
01:31:28,544 --> 01:31:31,449
I've never been hated
like that before.

1249
01:31:31,903 --> 01:31:33,897
Then, that
must have been difficult..

1250
01:31:33,898 --> 01:31:35,728
Yes...

1251
01:31:36,274 --> 01:31:37,143
very.

1252
01:31:41,093 --> 01:31:45,007
Nowadays people want glamour,
and tears, the grand performance.

1253
01:31:45,008 --> 01:31:47,580
I'm not very good at that,
I never have been...

1254
01:31:48,923 --> 01:31:51,304
I prefer to keep
my feelings to myself.

1255
01:31:52,481 --> 01:31:56,045
And foolishly I believed that was
what people wanted from their Queen...

1256
01:31:56,046 --> 01:31:59,336
not to make a fuss, nor wear one's
heart on one's sleeve...

1257
01:31:59,337 --> 01:32:01,571
duty first, self second.

1258
01:32:02,980 --> 01:32:05,008
That's how I was brought up...

1259
01:32:06,386 --> 01:32:08,328
that's all I've ever known.

1260
01:32:08,329 --> 01:32:10,837
You were so young
when you became Queen.

1261
01:32:17,180 --> 01:32:18,236
Yes...

1262
01:32:20,229 --> 01:32:21,728
Yes, a girl.

1263
01:32:27,028 --> 01:32:29,885
But I can see
that the world has changed...

1264
01:32:30,825 --> 01:32:34,183
and one must.. modernise.

1265
01:32:36,060 --> 01:32:38,809
Well, perhaps that's where I can help.

1266
01:32:40,631 --> 01:32:42,596
Don't get ahead of yourself,
Prime Minister, and remember...

1267
01:32:42,597 --> 01:32:45,161
I am the one
supposed to be advising you.

